. Tffls poem is written in close connection with the last. Instead of offering to share in the perilssof the war-as Horace before Actium in Epod. 1. 1—the poet explains why he must stand aside. He has no thirst for riches; conquered and conqueror alike will pass empty-handed into Acheron. Love and Song are his delight: when old age takes these away, he will scan the Laws of Nature, and peer into the secrets that lie beyond the grave.
